Two businessmen have been charged with stealing electronic goods worth Sh20 million from a private company in Nairobi. Joseph Munga Chege and Moses Mwaura allegedly stole CCTV Cameras, monitors screens, computers, TVs, Vibrators, grinders and Cartons from Alcoho company on November 25 along the Eastern by-passÂ while armed with a pistol. Police said the two were pretending to be Kenya Revenue Authority Staff. They both denied the charges before Kibera Magistrate Esther Boke and were released on a bond of Sh2 million each. The case will be heard on March 22. Click here for the latest political news